 juni 1170","1125":"1125","1202":"1202","1144":"1144","1150":"1150","1161":"1161","1170":"1170","1109":"1109","Bridport, Dorset, England":"Bridport, Dorset, England","Kirkoswald, Cumberland, England":"Kirkoswald, Cumbraland, England","Wraxall, Somerset, England":"Wraxall, Somerset, England","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England","Mitford Castle, , Northumberland, England":"Mitford, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1125–30 June 1170":"1125–30 juni 1170","1109–1161":"1109–1161","1150–1202":"1150–1202","1125–1170":"1125–1170","30 June 1170":"30 juni 1170","1125":"1125","1202":"1202","1144":"1144","1150":"1150","1161":"1161","1170":"1170","1109":"1109","Bridport, Dorset, England":"Bridport, Dorset, England","Kirkoswald, Cumberland, England":"Kirkoswald, Cumberland, England","Wraxall, Somerset, England":"Wraxall, Somerset, England","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England","Mitford Castle, , Northumberland, England":"Mitford, Northumberland, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1125–30 June 1170":"1125–30 June 1170","1109–1161":"1109–1161","1150–1202":"1150–1202","1125–1170":"1125–1170","30 June 1170":"30 June 1170","1125":"1125","1202":"1202","1144":"1144","1150":"1150","1161":"1161","1170":"1170","1109":"1109","Bridport, Dorset, England":"Bridport, Dorset, England","Kirkoswald, Cumberland, England":"Kirkoswald, Cumberland, England","Wraxall, Somerset, England":"Wraxall, Somerset, England","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England","Mitford Castle, , Northumberland, England":"Mitford, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Moreville","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Moorfield  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Moorfield","meanings":["English: locative name from Morville (Shrops), which is recorded as  <i>Mamerfeld</i> in the 12th century,  <i>Momerefeld</i> in 1255, and  <i>Morfelde</i> in 1464."]}]},{"name":"Matilda","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathilda","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Matilda de Moreville was born in 1125, in Kirkoswald, Cumberland, England. She married William de Morville in 1144, in Dorset, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died on 30 June 1170, in Mitford, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 45."},"et":{"1125–30 June 1170":"1125–30. juuni 1170","1109–1161":"1109–1161","1150–1202":"1150–1202","1125–1170":"1125–1170","30 June 1170":"30. juuni 1170","1125":"1125","1202":"1202","1144":"1144","1150":"1150","1161":"1161","1170":"1170","1109":"1109","Bridport, Dorset, England":"Bridport, Dorset, England","Kirkoswald, Cumberland, England":"Kirkoswald, Cumberland, England","Wraxall, Somerset, England":"Wraxall, Somerset, England","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England","Mitford Castle, , Northumberland, England":"Mitford, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1125–30 June 1170":"1125–30. kesäkuuta 1170","1109–1161":"1109–1161","1150–1202":"1150–1202","1125–1170":"1125–1170","30 June 1170":"30. kesäkuuta 1170","1125":"1125","1202":"1202","1144":"1144","1150":"1150","1161":"1161","1170":"1170","1109":"1109","Bridport, Dorset, England":"Bridport, Dorset, England","Kirkoswald, Cumberland, England":"Kirkoswald, Cumberland, England","Wraxall, Somerset, England":"Wraxall, Somerset, England","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England","Mitford Castle, , Northumberland, England":"Mitford, Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1125–30 June 1170":"1125–30 juin 1170","1109–1161":"1109–1161","1150–1202":"1150–1202","1125–1170":"1125–1170","30 June 1170":"30 juin 1170","1125":"1125","1202":"1202","1144":"1144","1150":"1150","1161":"1161","1170":"1170","1109":"1109","Bridport, Dorset, England":"Bridport, Dorset, Angleterre","Kirkoswald, Cumberland, England":"Kirkoswald, Cumberland, Angleterre","Wraxall, Somerset, England":"Wraxall, Somerset, Angleterre",